ne” reliability model\n\nNewest-first is better for UI freshness, but it is the wrong default for the transport fetch API in this system. It would maximize gap creation and, under bounded fetch, can keep older mail perpetually behind the hot edge.\n\nMy recommendation for `#67` is:\n- cursor-based pagination\n- oldest-first\n- cursor based on mailbox row identity / insertion order, not message timestamps\n- UI remains free to display newest-first after ingest\n\nGiven that, do you want me to implement `#67` as oldest-first cursor pagination from the node fetch API?\n\n<oai-mem-citation>\n<citation_entries>\nMEMORY.md:35-35|note=[quick pass found no issue-67-specific guidance beyond avoiding generic fixes without repo context]\n</citation_entries>\n<rollout_ids>\n</rollout_ids>\n</oai-mem-citation>",
