ery_cancel` is `None`.\n- `shutdown_discovery()` becomes a clean `if let Some(state) = self.discovery.take() { ... }` with no three separate `take()` calls.\n- The construction site returns `Option<DiscoveryState>` instead of a 3-tuple with two `(None, None, None)` exit paths.\n\n---\n\n#### Finding 2: Port extraction from `http_bind` is fragile -- use `SocketAddr` parsing\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, lines 724-728\n\n**Current code:**\n```rust\nlet port: u16 = http_bind\n    .rsplit(':')\n    .next()\n    .and_then(|p| p.parse().ok())\n    .unwrap_or(23004);\n```\n\nThis breaks for IPv6 addresses like `[::1]:8080` (would try to parse `8080` correctly by luck, but `[::]:8080` also works by accident). It silently falls back to a magic number `23004` on any parse failure.\n\n**Suggested simplification:**\n\n```rust\nlet port: u16 = http_bind\n    .parse::<std::net::SocketAddr>()\n    .map(|addr| addr.port())\n    .unwrap_or(23004);\n```\n\n**Why it is better:**\n- Correctly handles both IPv4 and IPv6 bind addresses.\n- Uses the standard library's battle-tested parser instead of ad-hoc string splitting.\n- Same fallback behavior, but the happy path is more robust.\n\n---\n\n#### Finding 3: Routing key computation is duplicated\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, lines 696-707 (discovery contact loading) and line 654 (`our_routing_key`)\n\n**Current code (discovery block):**\n```rust\nlet contacts: Vec<(PublicID, [u8; 16])> = storage\n    .list_contacts()\n    .unwrap_or_else(|e| { ... })\n    .into_iter()\n    .map(|(_, pubkey, _)| {\n        let rk: [u8; 16] = pubkey.routing_key().into();\n        (pubkey, rk)\n    })\n    .collect();\n```\n\nAnd separately at line 654:\n```rust\nlet our_routing_key = identity.public_id().routing_key();\n```\n\nAnd at line 730:\n```rust\nlet our_rk: [u8; 16] = identity.public_id().routing_key().into();\n```\n\nThe `routing_key().into()` pattern for `[u8; 16]` conversion appears twice. This is minor, but worth noting: `our_routing_key` (line 654) could be reused at line 730 instead of recomputing from `identity.public_id()`.\n\n**Suggested simplification:** Compute `our_routing_key` once before the coordinator subscribe call, then reuse it:\n\n```rust\nlet our_routing_key = identity.public_id().routing_key();\nlet (coordinator_events, coordinator_handle) = coordinator.subscribe(our_routing_key);\n\n// ... later in discovery block:\nlet our_rk: [u8; 16] = our_routing_key.into();\n```\n\nThis avoids the redundant `identity.public_id().routing_key()` call at line 730.\n\n**Why it is better:** Single source of truth for the local routing key. Trivial change, but removes a subtle duplication.\n\n---\n\n#### Finding 4: `shutdown_discovery()` has unnecessary granularity (relates to Finding 1)\n\n**File:** `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, lines 949-970\n\n**Current code:**\n```rust\nasync fn shutdown_discovery(&mut self) {\n    if let Some(cancel) = self.discovery_cancel.take() {\n        debug!(\"Cancelling discovery controller...\");\n        cancel.cancel();\n    }\n    if let Some(task) = self.discovery_task.take() {\n        debug!(\"Waiting for discovery controller to stop...\");\n        if let Err(e) = task.await { ... }\n    }\n    if let Some(backend) = self.discovery_backend.take() {\n        debug!(\"Shutting down mDNS backend...\");\n        if let Err(e) = backend.shutdown().await { ... }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThree independent `if let Some` blocks that logically form one operation.\n\n**Suggested simplification (with `DiscoveryState` from Finding 1):**\n```rust\nasync fn shutdown_discovery(&mut self) {\n    let Some(state) = self.discovery.take() else {\n        return;\n    };\n\n    debug!(\"Shutting down discovery subsystem...\");\n    state.cancel.cancel();\n\n    if let Some(task) = state.controller_task {\n        if let Err(e) = task.await {\n            warn!(error = %e, \"Discovery