es → shared constant (Medium)\n- Missing `PartialEq` derives on types → simpler tests (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 2: Transport Capabilities (`crates/reme-transport/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **M6 — MQTT quorum path** (`coordinator.rs:663-676`): HTTP targets correctly filtered by `targets_where(|c| c.quorum_credit)`. MQTT uses `pool.all_targets()` — no capability filter. `quorum_target_count`/`quorum_target_ids` DO filter MQTT, creating an inconsistency between the count and the actual delivery set.\n\n- **`replace_target()` upsert semantics** (`pool.rs:143-150`): Always inserts `new_target` even if `old_id` not found. Pool doc says \"replacement\" but behavior is upsert. Coordinator doc correctly describes upsert.\n\n- **`fetch_from_targets` layered filter** (`pool.rs:623-659`): `fetch_once` falls back to `all_targets()`, then `fetch_from_targets` re-filters by capability. Correct but fragile — a fast-path optimization could bypass the filter.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- `subscribe()` silently returns empty channel when no HTTP pool configured.\n- `TargetConfig` struct literal syntax breaks with new `capabilities` field (acceptable for prototype stage).\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**High deviations:**\n\n- **M7 — `TransportRegistry` still has mutation methods**: Plan requires read-only conversion. `add_http_target()` and other mutators still present. Dual write authority.\n- **M8 — `MessageReceiver` not deprecated**: Still exported, no `#[deprecated]` attribute.\n\n**Medium deviations:**\n\n- **m7 — `stable_defaults()` has `replicate: false`**: Plan says all flags set for stable. No enforcement points exist for `replicate` yet.\n- `update_http_target` became `replace_http_target` — different name/signature but improved semantics.\n\n**Compliant:** `fetch_once` filters by FETCH, `submit_to_quorum_targets` filters by QUORUM_CREDIT, invariant tests present, booleans vs bitflags documented.\n\n#### Simplifier\n\nTop findings:\n- Derive `Default` on `TargetCapabilities` (Medium)\n- `quorum_target_count` via `quorum_target_ids().len()` — eliminate duplication (Medium)\n- Rename `targets_where` → `targets_by_capability` (Low)\n- Consistent delegation style in coordinator mutations (Low)\n- Doc comments reference bitflag-style names but implementation uses booleans (Low)\n\n---\n\n### Area 3: Discovery Controller (`apps/client/src/discovery/`)\n\n#### Code Review\n\n**Critical:**\n\n- **C3 — SEC-2 timing oracle** (`controller.rs:362-367`): `verify_peer_identity` returns on first matching candidate. Plan requires iterating all N candidates with constant-time final decision.\n\n- **C4 — SEC-3 channel binding missing** (`controller.rs:324-369`): `build_identity_sign_data` signs `\"reme-identity-v1:\" || challenge || node_pubkey`. No responder IP:port. MITM can relay challenge to real peer. No FIXME at call site.\n\n**Major:**\n\n- **`TargetId` constructed independently** (`controller.rs:240-260`): `PeerEntry.target_id` computed with `TargetId::http(url)` separately from the `HttpTarget`'s internal ID. Forward fragility if URL construction diverges.\n\n- **URL-unchanged short-circuit** (`controller.rs:157-169`): Skips re-verification when URL unchanged. No safety net — periodic refresh and stale-peer lifecycle not implemented.\n\n- **`expect()` in constructor** (`controller.rs:108`): `reqwest::Client::builder().build().expect(...)` panics inside a spawned task — silent crash.\n\n- **`max_peers=0` silently clamped** (`controller.rs:94`): No warning logged.\n\n**Minor:**\n\n- Shutdown uses `iter` + `clear()` instead of `drain()`.\n- `LanDiscoveryConfig` has no `max_peers > 0` validation.\n- Contact index collision test is artificial (same routing key assigned manually).\n\n#### Spec Review\n\n**Major deviations:**\n\n- **M9 — No periodic refresh**: No timer, no `tokio::time::interval`. `refresh_interval_secs` config field missing entirely.\n- **M10 — No stale-peer lifecycle**: No Suspended state, no failure counter, no `stale_timeout`.\n- **M