t). If `browse()` fails, re-acquire lock and reset `browsing = false`.\n\n5. **m5 — Simplify `stop_advertising`:** Hold lock through the entire method since `daemon.unregister()` is an in-process mpsc send. Remove the clone+split-lock pattern.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-discovery`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 2: TXT Helpers & Fake Backend (M5, m1, m2, m3, m6)\n\n**Files:** `crates/reme-discovery/src/txt.rs`, `crates/reme-discovery/src/fake.rs`, `crates/reme-discovery/src/types.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **M5 — Add v=2 test:** Add test `unsupported_version_2_is_rejected` verifying `decode_txt` returns `TxtError::InvalidVersion(\"2\")`.\n\n2. **m1 — Fix async tests:** Change 4 fake.rs tests that have no `.await` from `#[tokio::test] async fn` to `#[test] fn`: `inject_peer_and_receive`, `inject_updated_and_receive`, `inject_lost_and_receive`, `multiple_subscribers_receive_events`.\n\n3. **m2 — Unify channel capacity:** Add `pub(crate) const DISCOVERY_CHANNEL_CAPACITY: usize = 128;` to `types.rs`. Use it in both `fake.rs:21` and `mdns_sd.rs:39`.\n\n4. **m3 — Remove `version` param from `encode_txt`:** Hard-code `\"1\"` inside `encode_txt`. The version parameter is only ever called with `1` and the decoder rejects anything else. Update call site in `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs:731`.\n\n5. **m6 — Return named struct from `decode_txt`:** Replace `(RoutingKey, u16, u8)` with:\n   ```rust\n   pub struct TxtFields {\n       pub routing_key: RoutingKey,\n       pub port: u16,\n       pub version: u8,\n   }\n   ```\n   Update all call sites (controller.rs `decode_txt(&peer.txt_records)` destructure, all tests).\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-discovery && cargo test -p reme-client`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 3: Transport Capabilities Fixes (M6, m7, m8, m9, S3, S4, S5)\n\n**Files:** `crates/reme-transport/src/coordinator.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/target.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **M6 — MQTT quorum capability filter:** In `submit_to_quorum_targets()` line 667, change `pool.all_targets()` to `pool.targets_where(|c| c.quorum_credit)` for the MQTT path, matching the HTTP path.\n\n2. **m7 — Set `replicate: true` in `stable_defaults()`:** Align with plan spec. No enforcement points exist yet but the default should match the plan.\n\n3. **m8 — Document `replace_target` upsert semantics:** Update pool-level doc to explicitly state upsert behavior, matching coordinator-level doc.\n\n4. **m9 — Add comment to `fetch_from_targets`:** Document the layered capability filter intent so future refactors don't break the invariant.\n\n5. **S3 — Simplify `quorum_target_count`:** Implement as `self.quorum_target_ids(config).len() as u32`. Remove the duplicated ~20 lines.\n\n6. **S4 — Derive `Default` on `TargetCapabilities`:** Add `Default` derive (all false). Simplify `stable_defaults()` and `ephemeral_defaults()` with `..Self::default()`.\n\n7. **S5 — Rename `targets_where` → `targets_by_capability`:** For naming consistency with `targets_by_kind`.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-transport`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 4: Discovery Controller Security & Quality (C3, m10, m12, S6, S7)\n\n**Files:** `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **C3 — Fix SEC-2 timing oracle:** In `verify_peer_identity`, iterate ALL candidates without early return. Accumulate the first match in `Option<PublicID>`, continue iterating, return accumulated result:\n   ```rust\n   let mut matched: Option<PublicID> = None;\n   for candidate in candidates {\n       let sign_data = build_identity_sign_data(&challenge, &candidate.to_bytes());\n       if candidate.verify_xeddsa(&sign_data, &signature) && matched.is_none() {\n           matched = Some(*candidate);\n       }\n   }\n   Ok(matched)\n   ```\n\n2. **Add FIXME for C4 (SEC-3):** Add `// FIXME(SEC-3): channel binding not implemented — responder IP:port not in signed data` comment on `verify_peer_identity`.\n\n3. **m10 — Replace `expect()` with error propagation:** Change `DiscoveryController::new` to return `Result<Self, reqwest::Error>`. In `spawn()`, handle the error by logging and returning early.\n\n4. **m12 — Warn on `max_peers` clamp:** Add `warn!` when `max_peers` is clamped from 0 to 1.\n\n5. **S6 — Remove `target_id` from `PeerEntry`:** Compute `TargetId::http(&entry.url)` on the fly at the 3 usage sites. Eliminates field sync risk.\n\n6. **S7 — Add debug logging:** Add `debug!` to base64 decode failure (line 365) and signature length check failure (line 368).\n\n7. **Use `drain()` in shutdown:** Replace `for ... in &peer_index` + `peer_index.clear()` with `peer_index.drain()`.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-client`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 5: Client Runtime Simplifications (m14, S1, S2)\n\n**Files:** `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, `apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **S1 — `DiscoveryState` struct:** Add to `discovery/mod.rs`:\n   ```rust\n   pub struct DiscoveryState {\n       pub backend: Arc<MdnsSdBackend>,\n       pub cancel: CancellationToken,\n       pub controller_task: Option<JoinHandle<()>>,\n   }\n   ```\n   Replace the three `Option` fields in `App` with `discovery: Option<DiscoveryState>`.\n\n2. **S2 — Extract `discovery::initialize()`:** Move the ~65 lines from `App::new` (lines 688-753) into `pub async fn initialize(...)` in `discovery/mod.rs`. Return `Option<DiscoveryState>`.\n\n3. **m14 — Port extraction:** Replace `rsplit(':').next()` with `http_bind.parse::<std::net::SocketAddr>().map(|a| a.port()).unwrap_or(23004)`.\n\n4. **Simplify `shutdown_discovery`:** Single `if let Some(state) = self.discovery.take()` guard clause.\n\n5. **Don't create orphan CancellationToken** when `allow_direct_lan = false`.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-client && cargo clippy -p reme-client`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 6: Discovery Controller Features (M9, M10, M11)\n\n**Files:** `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs`, `apps/client/src/config.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **M9 — Periodic refresh:** Add `refresh_interval_secs: u64` to `LanDiscoveryConfig` (default 300). In the controller event loop, add a `tokio::time::interval` alongside the event stream. On tick, iterate all `peer_index` entries and re-verify their identity. On failure, remove the target.\n\n2. **M10 — Stale-peer lifecycle:** Track a `failure_count: u8` in `PeerEntry`. On verification failure during refresh, increment counter. At 2 failures (ephemeral circuit breaker), remove the peer and its target. On successful refresh, reset counter.\n\n3. **M11 — Add `verified_peer_index`:** Add `verified_peer_index: HashMap<PublicID, Vec<String>>` mapping PublicID to instance names. Maintain it alongside `peer_index` in `handle_new`, `handle_update`, `handle_lost`, and shutdown. This enables multi-device support (same identity on different devices).\n\n4. **Config name alignment (m11):** Rename `allow_direct_lan` to `auto_direct_known_contacts` in `LanDiscoveryConfig`. Update all references.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-client`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 7: Client Runtime Features (M12, M13, M14, m13)\n\n**Files:** `apps/client/src/tui/app.rs`, `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs`, `apps/client/src/tui/ui.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **M12 — Dynamic contact updates:** Add an `mpsc::UnboundedSender<(PublicID, [u8; 16])>` to the discovery controller. In `spawn()`, select on both the event stream and the contact channel. When a new contact arrives, insert it into `contact_index`. In `try_add_contact`, send the new contact through the channel.\n\n2. **M13 — TUI discovered-peer state:** Add a `discovered_peers: Vec<DiscoveredPeerInfo>` or similar read channel from the controller. Display peer count in the status bar area. (Minimal viable: just a count indicator.)\n\n3. **M14 — TUI notification when mDNS inactive:** When `lan_discovery.enabled = true` but mDNS init fails, set a status message visible in the TUI (not just file log).\n\n4. **m13 — Migrate to `send_text_tiered`:** Replace `client.send_text()` with `client.send_text_tiered()` in the TUI send handler. Surface the `TieredDeliveryPhase` in the status message.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test -p reme-client && cargo clippy -p reme-client`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 8: Transport Registry & MessageReceiver (M7, M8)\n\n**Files:** `crates/reme-transport/src/registry.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/receiver.rs`, `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **M7 — Convert TransportRegistry to read-only view:** Remove `add_http_target()` and other mutation methods from `TransportRegistry`. Add `with_coordinator()` constructor that reads pool state from the coordinator. Remove `with_composite()`. Update all call sites.\n\n2. **M8 — Deprecate MessageReceiver:** Add `#[deprecated(since = \"0.4.0\", note = \"Use TransportCoordinator::subscribe() instead\")]` to `MessageReceiver`, `ReceiverConfig`, `ReceiverHandle`. Verify no remaining consumers.\n\n**Verification:** `cargo test --workspace && cargo clippy --workspace`\n\n---\n\n## Unit 9: Node API & Documentation (m15, m16, doc fixes)\n\n**Files:** `apps/node/src/api.rs`, `docs/threat-model.md`, `AGENTS.md`\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **m15 — Zeroize `sign_data` in `get_identity`:** Add `use zeroize::Zeroize;`, change `let sign_data` to `let mut sign_data`, add `sign_data.zeroize()` after capturing signature. Matches `generate_receipt` pattern.\n\n2. **m16 — Fix threat model MAX_PEERS reference:** Change \"MAX_PEERS in apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs\" to \"configurable peer cap (default: 256, via `LanDiscoveryConfig.max_peers`)\".\n\n3. **Update module doc in api.rs:** List all 6 endpoints with auth classification.\n\n4. **Fix threat model §2 residual risk:** Add contact-graph edge mention.\n\n5. **Fix orphaned `## LAN Discovery` heading:** Promote numbered sections to `###` under it.\n\n6. **Remove duplicate HTML comment TODO** in threat model §2.\n\n7. **Reconcile channel binding status:** Update threat model to say \"deferred\" not \"rejected\" to align with plan